      <div class="container static_text">
        <h1> Search Help </h1>
          <p>
            Powo has a free text search with a number of advanced features, which are explained below:
          </p>
          <h3>Multiple Search Terms</h3>
          <p>Typing a search and hitting “enter” allows you to type a second term in the search bar.
            These restrict the results of the previous search. (i.e, a search for “orchidaceae”, “yellow flowers”
             and “africa” would give a list of all orchids with yellow flowers in africa.)
             Individual search terms can be deleted by pressing the x on each one.
          </p>
          <p><a class="document_links" href="/?f=has_images&q=africa%2Cyellow+flowers%2COrchidaceae">Try it here</a><p>
          <h3>Operators</h3>
          <p>
            Putting a field name and a colon at the start of your search will restrict the search to the selected field
            (i.e, “flowers: yellow” will restrict the search to only taxa that have the word yellow in the flower description)
          </p>
          <p>
            Currently, you can use the following field names:
          </p>
          <ul class="column_list">
            <li>Characteristics:</li>
            <li>summary</li>
            <li>appearance</li>
            <li>characteristic</li>
            <li>flower</li>
            <li>fruit</li>
            <li>leaf</li>
            <li>inflorescence</li>
            <li>seed</li>
            <li>cloning</li>
            <li>use</li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="column_list">
            <li>Names:</li>
            <li>name</li>
            <li>common name</li>
            <li>family</li>
            <li>genus</li>
            <li>kingdom</li>
            <li>species</li>
            <li>author</li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="column_list">
            <li class="heading">Geography:</li>
            <li>location</li>
          </ul>
      <p><a class="document_links" href="/?f=all_results&q=author%3A+L.">Try it here</a><p>
      </p>
      <p>
        Quotes around text, use of "and" or "or" do not have any effect
      </p>
      <h3>Filters</h3>
      <p>
        The filter bar allows you to quickly constrain results by some common terms. For example, you can use it to narrow searches down to results with images, or only families, genera or species.
      </p>
      <p>
        <p><a class="document_links" href="/?f=has_images%2Cfamily_f">Try it here</a><p>
      </p>
      <h3>TDWG and Geographical search</h3>
      <p>
        Powo uses TDWG regions for its geographical search. These are botanical regions that do not necessarily conform to country borders. Continents are searchable, as are continent sections (i.e West Siberia)
      </p>
      <p><a class="document_links" href="/?f=all_results&q=West+Siberia">Try it here</a><p>
